    • Method Detail

      • evaluateRPN

        public boolean evaluateRPN​(java.lang.String notation,
                           java.lang.String delimiter)
        Method that evaluates given RPN notation. The String is split and the numbers are moved onto stack, while the operators are read and corresponding calculations are made. The result is pushed back on stack.
        Parameters:
        notation - - user's input of RPN
        delimiter - - character used to split the String
        Returns:
        true if there was an error and user needs to fix their input, false otherwise

      • isNumeric

        public boolean isNumeric​(java.lang.String value)
        Method that checks whether the String value is a number.
        Parameters:
        value - - String that is being checked
        Returns:
        false/true depending on outcome of the test

      • calculate

        public boolean calculate​(java.lang.String operator)
        Performs calculations with numbers within the stack. The numbers from stack are popped and then corresponding to the operator, calculations are made.
        Parameters:
        operator - - an operator passed from the read input
        Returns:
        if there is an error, it returns true
